out of there to show that. And so while the

00:24:05.350 --> 00:24:12.710
initial research I was telling about provided
the content for the, the history part a lot,

00:24:12.710 --> 00:24:18.320
it is the people that I really stumbled upon
or they would stumble upon me 'cause I'm fixed

00:24:18.320 --> 00:24:23.201
in one spot but whoever came by, they're the
ones who provided the content for the street

00:24:23.201 --> 00:24:27.690
level, for the, the, the present views themselves.

00:24:27.690 --> 00:24:36.179
And so the entire mural has - so basically
the way I did that is I basically started

00:24:36.179 --> 00:24:42.220
by setting the stage. And I started drawing
the neighborhood and tried to put the markers

00:24:42.220 --> 00:24:47.279
that make it clear where it is. And immediately
as soon as it became clear, people started

00:24:47.279 --> 00:24:48.570
placing themselves in it.

00:24:48.570 --> 00:24:52.640
It's like, 'Oh, ah, I see...that's as soon
as I get – that's Jonas and Golden Gate.

00:24:52.640 --> 00:24:56.860
That's here. Put me right there. That's where
I live', you know? 'Put me over here with

00:24:56.860 --> 00:24:57.860
my friends'.

00:24:57.860 --> 00:25:05.670
And so people just started pointing out where
it is that they wanted to be. And so all I

00:25:05.670 --> 00:25:12.110
had to do was set the stage and they basically
directed the play with themselves as actors.

00:25:12.110 --> 00:25:17.899
And so because I couldn't always just stop
and paint them in because I started doing

00:25:17.899 --> 00:25:22.370
this before I had even finished a background
and I couldn't really paint them, I took reference

00:25:22.370 --> 00:25:27.299
pictures so that I could copy them later.
And when I'm done I will give them the picture.

00:25:27.299 --> 00:25:33.160
And so in the background there's - there,
slowly, it's becoming a little populated and

00:25:33.160 --> 00:25:39.091
it became quite a gregarious little scene.
I would joke that I work at the Tenderloin

00:25:39.091 --> 00:25:47.860
Public Photo Booth 'cause like everybody would
come by and just [pause] - and so, and it

00:25:47.860 --> 00:25:57.710
was a great, great way to kind of - and what
this actually did was it really described

00:25:57.710 --> 00:26:00.419
the social geography of the place accurately.

00:26:00.419 --> 00:26:07.559
So this is the part of the mural that is not
a second, third hand, secondary, tertiary,

00:26:07.559 --> 00:26:12.610
et cetera, et cetera historical document.
